Their apprehensions stem from several anticipated changes in celestial bodies, specifically: 
* that the Earth, due to the Sun's gradual approach towards it, will eventually be absorbed or engulfed over time; 
* that the Sun's surface will progressively become encrusted with its own emissions, ultimately ceasing to illuminate the world; 
* that the Earth narrowly avoided a catastrophic encounter with the tail of the most recent comet, which would have inevitably reduced it to ashes; 
* and that the next predicted comet, calculated to arrive thirty-one years from now, will likely bring about our destruction.

In essence, this charter encompassed the following provisions: 
* The liberation of the Mother Church from past oppressions;
* Unencumbered succession for noble heirs to their ancestral lands, requiring only a moderate relief payment to the king, without additional redemption fees;
* Abolition of fines for granting marriage licenses to their female heirs, with the exception that license would be withheld if the proposed match was with the king's enemy;
* The appointment of next of kin as guardians for orphaned minors' lands;
* Establishment of punishments for those counterfeiting false currency;
* A confirmation of the laws of St. Edward; 
* And a general pardon, granting amnesty to all.
